00:23:00.420 --> 00:23:03.600 align:middle line:84%
So sometimes, people also
use the following object--

00:23:03.600 --> 00:23:10.440 align:middle line:84%
the G A equal to minus
t, t prime minus t.

00:23:10.440 --> 00:23:13.590 align:middle line:84%
So only it's non-zero
when t prime is

00:23:13.590 --> 00:23:16.170 align:middle line:90%
greater than t and the delta.

00:23:16.170 --> 00:23:16.850 align:middle line:90%
Oh, sorry.

00:23:16.850 --> 00:23:19.310 align:middle line:90%
Here, it should be x, x prime.

00:23:19.310 --> 00:23:25.440 align:middle line:90%


00:23:25.440 --> 00:23:28.590 align:middle line:84%
And finally, you
can define an object

00:23:28.590 --> 00:23:31.920 align:middle line:90%
called G F which is half--

00:23:31.920 --> 00:23:33.390 align:middle line:90%
so this is called the retarded.

00:23:33.390 --> 00:23:35.670 align:middle line:84%
This is called
advanced, which is

00:23:35.670 --> 00:23:38.760 align:middle line:84%
like half of the retarded
and half advanced.

00:23:38.760 --> 00:23:44.450 align:middle line:84%
So when t greater than t
prime, you take the G plus.

00:23:44.450 --> 00:23:47.690 align:middle line:90%
And when t is greater than--

00:23:47.690 --> 00:23:50.390 align:middle line:90%
t prime greater than t--

00:23:50.390 --> 00:23:51.650 align:middle line:90%
let me do it here--

00:23:51.650 --> 00:23:58.810 align:middle line:90%


00:23:58.810 --> 00:24:00.190 align:middle line:90%
you do G minus.

00:24:00.190 --> 00:24:03.700 align:middle line:90%


00:24:03.700 --> 00:24:06.670 align:middle line:84%
Again, this G F is a
function of x and x prime.

00:24:06.670 --> 00:24:09.850 align:middle line:90%


00:24:09.850 --> 00:24:12.340 align:middle line:84%
So because they don't commute,
so these are various objects

00:24:12.340 --> 00:24:14.140 align:middle line:90%
you can define.

00:24:14.140 --> 00:24:15.940 align:middle line:90%
So one second.

00:24:15.940 --> 00:24:20.680 align:middle line:84%
So at the moment, they may seem
