01:00:28.545 --> 01:00:32.160 align:middle line:90%


01:00:32.160 --> 01:00:33.690 align:middle line:90%
So for t equal to t prime--

01:00:33.690 --> 01:00:36.380 align:middle line:90%


01:00:36.380 --> 01:00:39.800 align:middle line:84%
so the integral
becomes following--

01:00:39.800 --> 01:00:43.685 align:middle line:84%
G plus x and x prime
just equal to--

01:00:43.685 --> 01:00:58.370 align:middle line:90%


01:00:58.370 --> 01:01:01.230 align:middle line:90%
just become this.

01:01:01.230 --> 01:01:04.460 align:middle line:84%
And this integral
clearly is non-zero.

01:01:04.460 --> 01:01:09.830 align:middle line:84%
So that's why we said earlier,
this is not a localized state.

01:01:09.830 --> 01:01:14.330 align:middle line:84%
So this is equal to
this x and x prime.

01:01:14.330 --> 01:01:17.570 align:middle line:84%
So this is non-zero as
equal to, and so this is not

01:01:17.570 --> 01:01:20.580 align:middle line:90%
